# Desktop shell — reload after edits (required)

If this session **changed any file** under `nature-cortana-platform/desktop-shell/` (including `src/overlay.js`, `src/cortana-hologram-system.js`, `src/overlay.html`, `src/overlay.css`, `assets/`, `scripts/`, `src/preload.cjs`, `src/main.cjs`), **before you finish your reply** you **must** run:

```bash
cd nature-cortana-platform/desktop-shell && npm run reload
```

This POSTs to the dev reload server (default `127.0.0.1:4749`, or next free port — `reload_overlay.cjs` reads `~/Library/Application Support/nature-cortana-desktop-shell/dev-reload-port.txt` when present). Requires the app to have been started with `CORTANA_DEV_RELOAD_SERVER=1` (`npm start` / `npm run start:hero`).

- If reload fails (connection refused / timeout), say so and ask the user to start Cortana once, then they can run `npm run reload` manually.
- **Main** (`main.cjs`) or **preload** changes still need a **full quit + `npm start`** — HTTP reload only refreshes the renderer.

Skip `npm run reload` only when **no** desktop-shell files were modified in this turn.
